div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, hold- ing Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
James H Woolery, Cheif of The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County. Greeting Police of Seattle King Co Wash Terry

We command you, that you have the body of Ah Korn by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such impris- onment and detention, by whatsoever name said Ah Korn shall be called or chargedm before the HON. ROGER S GREENE, Judge of the aforesaid Court at three Oclock PM of this 11th day of September 1884 to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the said Ah Korn And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 11th day of Sept A. D. 1884
JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk. By James P Ludlow Deputy
